content.description: Climb thin fingers and fingers up a flake to a ledge.  Continue up and right passing two bolts on the exposed arete.
content.protection: Finger-sized cam for start, 2 QDs, and a 2 bolt anchor.
content.location: This is the leftmost route on the wall.  See the beta photo on the main page.

content.description: Climb a left-leaning, tips splitter with pods to easy face climbing.
content.location: See the beta photo on the main page.

content.description: Begin with stemming and compression in a corner up to a hand jam and then an overhanging V-slot roof.  Pass the roof with a gnarly kneebar and the climbing eases above.
content.protection:
Gray Metolius through fingers.  It shares anchors with

Rollercoaster of Love

.  The gear can be a little tricky to place at the roof due to the irregular nature of the crack.
content.location: See the beta photo on the main page.

content.description: Climb a slab up to a roof.  Pass the roof with powerful laybacking (crux), and face climb to the chains.
content.location: See the beta photo on the main page.

content.description:
Begin with powerful laybacking right off the deck (crux).  Layback up ~10 feet and get established on the face.  Follow discontinuous cracks and face holds to the chains.  This shares anchors with

Soul Reaver

.

Don't let the bottom scare you away, it's really fun.
content.location: See the beta photo on the main page.

content.description: Climb splitter fingers on a slab up to a small roof.  Work around roof with laybacking up and right to a boulder problem ending with a handjam.  Follow jugs to the chains.
content.location: See the beta photo on the main page.

content.description: Face climb and stem up to a bolt and mantle onto a ledge.  Follow a low angle corner to the chains.
content.location: See the beta photo on the main page.

content.description: This is a gear protected face climb, it is super fun for the grade.
content.protection: The gear is a little tricky.  Here's what I placed in order:  yellow C3, #2 Friend, green C3 and #0.4 Camalot.  There are a few other options for small stuff.
content.location: See the beta photo on the main page.

content.description:
Climb a delicate slab to a decent stance and clip a bolt.  Continue up and left using a tips flake and clip another bolt at the roof.  Traverse out under the roof to a good hold, pull up into the weakness using a sloper (crux), and pass one more bolt to the chains.

It is short but really fun.
content.location:
This is just right of

Zod the Immortal

.  See the beta photo on the main page.
